      "marks": 4,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "i",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "Which of the following quadratic equations represents the given situation?",
          "answer": "(B)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $x^2 + 3x - 35 = 0$",
            "(B) $x^2 + 3x - 70 = 0$",
            "(C) $x^2 - 3x - 70 = 0$",
            "(D) $x^2 + 70x - 3 = 0$"
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "ii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Find the roots of the quadratic equation obtained in part (i) using the discriminant method.",
          "answer": "$x = 7$ and $x = -10$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Identify coefficients: $a = 1, b = 3, c = -70$.",
              "Calculate discriminant $D = b^2 - 4ac = (3)^2 - 4(1)(-70) = 9 + 280 = 289$.",
              "Use quadratic formula $x = \\frac{-b \\pm \\sqrt{D}}{2a}$.",
              "Calculate $x = \\frac{-3 \\pm \\sqrt{289}}{2} = \\frac{-3 \\pm 17}{2}$.",
              "Solve for $x$: $x_1 = \\frac{14}{2} = 7$ and $x_2 = \\frac{-20}{2} = -10$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$D = (3)^2 - 4(1)(-70) = 9 + 280 = 289 \\\\ x = \\frac{-3 \\pm \\sqrt{289}}{2} \\\\ x = \\frac{-3 \\pm 17}{2} \\\\ x = 7, -10$"
          }
        },
